            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1583501913226-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>cubed paneer</strong>,<strong> sliced pepper</strong> and <strong>tomato wedges</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for 5-6 min further or until the paneer is golden and the pepper is starting to soften, turning the paneer occasionally for even colouring</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[180ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583501916573-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583501916573-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583501916573-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583501916573-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583501916573-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan, give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of vegetable oil if the pan looks a little dry</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>paneer jalfrezi</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583501920067-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583501920067-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583501920067-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583501920067-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583501920067-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>paneer jalfrezi</strong> over the <strong>jeera rice</strong></p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into small bowls and turn out</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
